{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774471402,"nonce":"+tqFHBApdhrju2nYG+Zz6PsDc1c=","message":"**Diagnosis update: recompilation is per-batch, not per-inner-step**\n\nWith JAX_LOG_COMPILES=1 locally:\n- _adversary_update: 2 compilations total (initial + weak_type stabilization) — FIXED\n- _loss_and_force_grad: ~2 compilations per adversarial batch (10 for 5 batches)\n- _controller_step: ~2 compilations per adversarial batch (10 for 5 batches)\n\nThe adversary weak_type fix worked. But _loss_and_force_grad and _controller_step still recompile. Treedefs of all arguments (model, trial_specs, forces) are verified identical across batches. The recompilation trigger is in eqx.filter_jit's cache key — it may use stricter equality than treedef (e.g., non-array leaf VALUE equality, not just structure equality).\n\nNext steps:\n1. Check if eqx.filter_jit treats non-array leaves (Python ints, strings in the model) as static cache keys\n2. If so, the model's non-array leaves (like string labels, population indices) are being included in the cache key even though they never change — but object identity might differ after apply_updates\n3. Potential fix: use jax.jit with explicit donate_argnums/static_argnums, or pre-partition into static/dynamic parts once\n\nOn TPU, each recompilation takes 30+ min. Locally, ~1s each. This is why TPU training hangs — 2 recompilations per batch × 30 min = never finishes.","files":null}]}